items.title: Market snaps 2-week fall, rupee hits fresh record low
items.description: In this week, the Indian rupee hit fresh record low of 84.50 but ended 5 paise lower at 84.45 per dollar on November 22 against the November 14 closing of 84.40.

items.title: Jigar Patel sees Nifty marching towards 24,500, picks these 3 ideas with sentiment revival
items.description: The Nifty 50’s breakout from a falling trendline indicates a potential retest of 24,500, though upcoming Maharashtra election results and geopolitical uncertainties could affect sentiment.
